geneVariantDescriptions.description: AURKA L364S lies within transactivation domain 3 of the Aurka protein (PMID: 26782714). L364S, combined with L363A, results in transactivation and MYC promoter usage similar to wild-type Aurka in cell culture (PMID: 26782714), but has not been individually characterized and therefore, its effect on Aurka protein function is unknown.

references.title: Nuclear AURKA acquires kinase-independent transactivating function to enhance breast cancer stem cell phenotype.
